[The estimated mortality directly attributable to the SARS-CoV-2 pandemic in the USA is approximately 300 000. With an estimated 10-20% of the population infected, there have been approximately 300 000 deaths, do the math of mortality that might occur if one ponders using the herd immunity approach. And note that the age and ethnic group most experiencing the excess mortality are the 25-44-year-olds, and overall among the Hispanic ethnic group.

Prior ProMED-mail posts focused on excess mortality include COVID-19 update (443): cytokine storm, mortality comparison, WHO, global 20201018.7870550 and COVID-19 update (380): excess mortality, 2nd infect, pediatric shedding, WHO 20200829.7727737, the latter looking at France. The toll the pandemic has been taking is massive. - Mod.MPP]

